### Case Management API — REST Client
### Default profile (`http`): port 5082. For HTTPS use `https://localhost:7277` and `--launch-profile https`.
### Requires valid `Database` and `Jwt` config (see appsettings / user secrets) for the API to start.
###
### Integration flow (manual):
### 1) Sign in or sign up — copy `accessToken` from JSON into @accessToken; copy `refresh_token` value from `Set-Cookie` into @refreshCookie (REST Client does not jar cookies).
### 2) GET /auth/me with Bearer — expect 200.
### 3) Wait until access JWT expires (Development uses Jwt:ExpiryMinutes, e.g. 5) — same GET — expect 401.
### 4) POST /auth/refresh with Cookie header — expect 200 and new access token; paste new values into @accessToken (and cookie if rotated).
### 5) GET /auth/me again with new Bearer — expect 200.

@api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5082
@accessToken = paste-access-token-here
@refreshCookie = paste-refresh-cookie-value-here

### Root — service name and status
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/
Accept: application/json

###

### Health — ASP.NET health checks (includes PostgreSQL when configured)
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/health

###

### OpenAPI document (Development only)
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/openapi/v1.json
Accept: application/json

###

### Swagger UI — open in a browser (Development only)
# https://localhost:7277/swagger
# {{api_HostAddress}}/swagger

###

### Sign up — same response shape as sign-in; sets HttpOnly refresh cookie (see Set-Cookie)
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/auth/sign-up
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ada",
  "lastName": "Lovelace",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "password": "your-password-8-chars-min"
}

###

### Sign in — issues JWT in body and sets HttpOnly refresh cookie (see Set-Cookie in response)
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/auth/sign-in
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "your-password"
}

###

### Me — protected; set @accessToken after sign-in/sign-up
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Refresh access token — refresh token is read only from the HttpOnly cookie (never from JSON).
### Set @refreshCookie from the sign-in/sign-up `Set-Cookie` body value, or use:
###   Cookie: refresh_token=<value>
### (cookie name matches Jwt:RefreshToken:CookieName in appsettings, default `refresh_token`).
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/auth/refresh
Cookie: refresh_token={{refreshCookie}}

###

### Sign out — clears refresh cookie when sent
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/auth/sign-out
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: refresh_token={{refreshCookie}}

{}

###
